cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.NI 

The paper discusses targeted immunization strategies for controlling epidemics, which is a topic related to social networks and their dynamics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses a synthetic benchmark with controlled community structure, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper uses the SIR epidemiological model, which is a mathematical model, indicating that it may belong to cs.MA (Mathematical Aspects) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
